      <title>The Agent Management Extension</title>
      <para>In a typical quantum deployment, there will be some agents running on network or compute nodes,
      such as quantum-dhcp-agent, quantum-ovs-agent and quantum-l3-agent. This extension provides a way
      for administrators to view their status. To update the agent needs upper layer feature's support.
      For example, administrators can disable one certain agent, and then quantum schedulers will not schedule
      resource to it.</para>
      <para>For how to use agent management extension and quantum schedulers feature,
      please refer to quantum admin guide.</para>
            <informaltable rules="all" width="100%">
